<p>[This is a Twitter Hack walk-through. How I got hacked, and willingly gave up my password to the scam. RE: <strong>StalkTrak</strong>, <strong>LTwitteri(d0t)com</strong>, <strong>"who's stalking your twitter."</strong> I've done it so you don't have to. Another popular variant, DM "Is this you in this picture &lt;link&gt;?"]</p>
<p><strong>Update 7-20-11:</strong> Just got this in my Direct Message inbox on Tweetdeck. The hack is still running folks.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-Shot-2011-07-20-at-11.50.22-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21611" title="StalkTrak, LTwitteri(d0t)com, Twitter Hack" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-Shot-2011-07-20-at-11.50.22-PM.png" alt="Screen Shot 2011 07 20 at 11.50.22 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="178" height="110" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Update (24 hrs):</strong> Steps: 1. UnAuthorize App, 2. Change Twitter Password. Seems to have done the trick, no further intrusions. Stay safe out there.</p>
<p>What was I thinking? I got what looked like a legitimate message about a new Twitter tool. And something about stalking. Perhaps that should&#039;ve been the clue. But I went along for a looksee. And in the process opened my account up to a scam of some sort. Here&#039;s how it got started.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.39.42-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19410" title="StalkTrak, LTwitteri(d0t)com, Twitter Hack" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.39.42-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.39.42 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="241" height="62" /></a></p>
<p>Not sure what &#034;stalks&#034; means in this case, but I&#039;m interested to find out.</p>
<p>Here&#039;s what the site logo and URL look like.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.43.04-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19419" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="Twitter Virus, Twitter Hack, Twitter Scam" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.43.04-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.43.04 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="171" height="122" /></a></p>
<p>They ask for an email address and a password.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.47.17-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19421" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="StalkTrak asks for Twitter Authorization AND email and password" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.47.17-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.47.17 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="412" height="323" /></a></p>
<p>And on the same screen is a Twitter OAuth link. It&#039;s odd to have both on one screen. I was curious, and I was feeling somewhat bulletproof. So I authorized the &#034;StalkTrak&#034; to see what was what.</p>
<p>Regardless of what you put in, here is the resulting page.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.47.45-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19422" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="StalkTrak Twitter Scam, twitter hack" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.47.45-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.47.45 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="513" height="310" /></a></p>
<p>And that was it. Nothing. I couldn&#039;t tell anything from this mash of data and for a few hours, nothing suspicious happened.</p>
<p>And then late last night these started going out as DM message from me.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.51.37-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19426" title="StalkTrak, LTwitteri(d0t)com, Twitter Hack" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.51.37-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.51.37 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="192" height="222" /></a></p>
<p>Okay, so I went back to Twitter and revolked the Twitter OAuthorization. Here&#039;s how you do that:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;"><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-7.15.03-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19439" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="Edit your Profile on Twitter.com" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-7.15.03-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 7.15.03 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="152" height="90" /></a></p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">And go to the</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;"><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-7.15.18-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19440" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="Applications screen on Twitter.com to kill Authorizations" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-7.15.18-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 7.15.18 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="435" height="181" /></a></p>
<p>And I was comfortable that I was done.  And I posted a few warning Tweets to alert anyone that had gotten a DM from me about LTitteri.com not to click on it.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.35.15-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19411" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="Alerting the masses to the LTwitteri twitter hack" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.35.15-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.35.15 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="416" height="150" /></a></p>
<p>And so at that point I figured I was done.</p>
<p>Until I checked back into my Twitter account. And found these lovely tidbits. I can see how these might really pose a problem for some folks. I think I&#039;m okay, though. I think&#8230; (grin)</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.34.47-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19409" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: black; border-style: solid;" title="Slanderous tweets could cause problems for some" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.34.47-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.34.47 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="420" height="295" /></a></p>
<p>Okay, so one more trip to Twitter to change my password. Yes, dumbass that I am, the password I gave in the LTwitteri screen WAS also my Twitter password. Now that was Dumb. My own dumbness, that I&#039;d been meaning to change for months. Okay, it&#039;s changed now.</p>
<p>And it looks like the Twitter Authorities are on the scam as well. When I tried to click one of the original links from the bogus Tweets, here&#039;s what I got.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.41.13-PM.png"><img title="Twitter scam caught by Twitter authorities" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-09-at-6.41.13-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 09 at 6.41.13 PM Twitter Hack Could Cause Problems: The Latest Hack Got My Password (StalkTrak)" width="371" height="167" /></a></p>
<p>Anyway, that&#039;s what it looks like when you walk into a Twitter ambush. You go off on a link from someone (I did not know the original &#034;stalk&#034; tweeter) and give authorization to an app and then your stream gets flooded with crap. I&#039;ve seen a similar scam on Facebook, usually with sex-ish topics in their pictures and subject lines.</p>
<p>Anyway, I wanted to warn you about  LTwitteri. Stay away, check your Twitter Authorizations and change your password. Stay safe out there.</p>
<p>@<a title="Looking to tweet safely" href="http://twitter.com/jmacofearth" target="_blank">jmacofearth</a><br />
permalink: <a href="http://uber.la/2011/07/twitter-hack/" target="_blank">http://uber.la/2011/07/twitter-hack/</a></p>
