ontent:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[
<p><span style="color: #888888;">[accidental #Transformers meme has skyrocketed this post, uh, thanks everybody ;-) And thanks to <strong>@<a title="A Tweeting Tips Maven from the Twin Cities" href="http://twitter.com/#!/tweetsmarter" target="_blank">tweetsmarter</a></strong> for starting a cascade of RT's. Here's the review: <a href="http://uber.la/2011/07/transformers-3/">Transformers 3: The Micro-Review</a>]</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #888888;">A bit over 10X a daily average for a post. Dang! Thanks again.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #888888;"><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-05-at-12.01.08-AM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17528" style="border: 1px solid black;" title="post goes viral with help from @tweetsmarter" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-05-at-12.01.08-AM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 05 at 12.01.08 AM Auto Bots Are Killing Twitter; Why Auto Social & Robot Social is Bad for Social" width="358" height="60" /></a></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>++ and now back to the post ++</p>
<p>Why are the Twitter continuance rates so bad? Why do so many people try Twitter and then leave? <strong>Up to 80% of new Twitter users will stop using the service within a month.</strong> What&#039;s wrong with this statistic? Is Twitter hard to use? Part of the problem is definitely the spammers.</p>
<p>Okay, so I&#039;ve written a lot about Twitter in the past few years. And some of it is &#034;how to&#034; some of it is &#034;here&#039;s how I think you should do it,&#034; and much of it is &#034;auto-bot, twitter spammers, and pornsters are killing twitter, here&#039;s how to fight back.&#034; So I guess there might be a problem. And it&#039;s not getting better.</p>
<p>Yesterday I was amazed when my Twitter Follower count (how many people are subscribed to my tweets) went up by several hundred in one day. What I was more amazed by was the list of some of my new followers.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-02-at-6.24.05-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17138" title="a new breed of Twitter spam" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-02-at-6.24.05-PM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 02 at 6.24.05 PM Auto Bots Are Killing Twitter; Why Auto Social & Robot Social is Bad for Social" width="313" height="418" /></a></p>
<p>And this was a long list. What&#039;s going on here?</p>
<p>Jibberish Twitter IDs and random names. What&#039;s the point? What&#039;s the game with creating a bunch of zombie Twitter accounts? How does that provide value or commerce for anything? And then this morning I am reminded of these type services.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-03-at-6.45.15-AM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17145" title="Tweet Adder does everything for you" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-03-at-6.45.15-AM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 03 at 6.45.15 AM Auto Bots Are Killing Twitter; Why Auto Social & Robot Social is Bad for Social" width="349" height="63" /></a></p>
<p>A site that will do it all for you. Let the robots do all your Twitter management. And guaranteed followers. Perhaps the two things are connected.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-03-at-6.44.14-AM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17146" title="And how they talk about themselves says a lot, SPAM" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Screen-shot-2011-07-03-at-6.44.14-AM.png" alt="Screen shot 2011 07 03 at 6.44.14 AM Auto Bots Are Killing Twitter; Why Auto Social & Robot Social is Bad for Social" width="635" height="119" /></a></p>
<p>Automatic Twitter Software. Ah, very nice. Auto what? Auto-SPAM. I love the idea of MASS TWEETS. What the heck do you suppose that is? Will this crap software write the tweets for you? In what language, ESL?</p>
<p>Okay, so Twitter is hard to learn. And trying to sift through the barrage of auto-SPAM-tweets is one of the most arduous tasks. And the &#034;adder&#034; &#8230; well,  different *adder* comes to mind when I see their name.</p>
<p><a href="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/tweetadder-joke.gif"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17147" title="tweetadder as adder" src="http://uber.la/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/tweetadder-joke.gif" alt="tweetadder joke Auto Bots Are Killing Twitter; Why Auto Social & Robot Social is Bad for Social" width="349" height="63" /></a></p>
<p>Yah know, the adder is a pretty bad ass snake, right?</p>
<p>Okay, so what can we do to fight back?</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Don&#039;t auto anything</strong>? In social auto is bad. It turns social into robot-social. And unless you are a machine or a coupon outlet, you need to express your humaness with every tweet.</li>
<li><strong>Report spammy Tweeters</strong>. You can use the &#034;Report as Spam function on Twitter.com&#034; or you can use a tool like <strong><a title="A quick way to eliminate spammy followers" href="http://www.twitblock.org/" target="_blank">TwitBlock</a></strong> to cull the crap.</li>
<li><strong>Use a tool like <a title="How to use Klout to improve your social media experience" href="http://uber.la/2011/06/klout/">Klout</a></strong> to up your own reputation online and learn what followers are REAL and which ones are bots.</li>
<li>And spread the word. <strong>Let people know that Auto-DMs piss you off</strong>.</li>
<li>Ask <a title="About geo-locating check-ins" href="http://uber.la/2010/09/goin-geo-i-am-the-mayor-of-my-mind/" target="_blank">auto-checkin friends</a> why they checked-in at McDonalds?</li>
<li>And then try and <strong>tweet like a human</strong>. As they say, you only get what you give.</li>
</ol>
